{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GpNoA128GjnyWG6exGRF9L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current state. I need to implement US-002: Render the box grid layout.\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n1. Create a config file with the 11 box labels (1-based, bottom-left to top-right)\n2. Create a grid rendering system that:\n   - Positions 11 boxes in a 3-3-3-2 layout (top three rows = 3 boxes, bottom row = 2 boxes centered)\n   - Top row = Tier 4 (current world order), bottom row = Tier 1 (deep structural forces)\n   - Each box has a text label\n   - Boxes have rounded corners, borders, and readable text\n   - Layout is centered and responsive for phone screens (375px-430px)\n\nFor PIXI.js, I'll use Graphics objects for the rounded box backgrounds and Text objects for the labels, positioning them according to the tier structure with boxes numbered 1-based from bottom-left to top-right.\n\nI'm organizing the code into separate modules: a config file for the box labels, a grid rendering module for the layout logic, and updating the main file to integrate everything. Now I need to work out the exact positioning—the visual layout from top to bottom shows Tier 4 at the top with boxes 9-11, then Tier 3 below that...\n\nFor the responsive design on mobile screens around 375px wide, I'm calculating that with padding and gaps between boxes, each of the three boxes per row should be roughly 106px wide, and I'll set the height to about 60px with appropriate vertical spacing between rows.\n\nNow I'm setting up a configuration with placeholder labels for the historical events since those can be swapped out easily later. I'll use realistic Danish-context examples that fit the timeline structure.\n\nBuilding the component now...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1276,"cache_read_input_tokens":28435,"cach