{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BNSKzpLxpMQuVbNUYaJGGC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- Project uses Vite + vanilla TypeScript (no framework)\n     3→- PIXI.js v8 for canvas rendering — use `new Application()` then `await app.init(...)` pattern\n     4→- Source code lives in `src/`\n     5→- npm is the package manager (no bun/pnpm)\n     6→- TypeScript strict mode enabled with `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters`\n     7→- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for typecheck, `npx vite build` for build\n     8→- Canvas is full-viewport with `resizeTo: window`, background `#1a1a2e`\n     9→- Box labels live in `src/config.ts` as a `BOX_LABELS` string array (0-based index, box 1 = index 0)\n    10→- Grid rendering lives in `src/grid.ts`, exports `createGrid(app)` → returns `BoxInfo[]`\n    11→- `BoxInfo` has `index`, `container`, `cx`, `cy`, `w`, `h` — needed for line drawing in future stories\n    12→- Connection logic lives in `src/connections.ts`, exports `setupConnections(app, boxes)` → returns `ConnectionManager`\n    13→- `ConnectionManager` has `connections: Connection[]` (mutable array) and `redraw()` to re-render all lines\n    14→- `Connection` interface: `{ source: number; target: number }` (0-based box indices)\n    15→- Lines use quadratic bezier curves with perpendicular offset, arrowheads at target box edge\n    16→- `touch-action: none` on canvas element prevents browser gestures from interfering with drag\n    17→\n    18→---\n    19→\n    20→## 2026-03-02 - US-001\n    21→- Set up Vite + TypeScript project scaffold\n    22→- Installed PIXI.js v8 and created full-viewport responsive canvas\n    23→- Canvas uses `resizeTo: window`, `autoDensity: true`, and `devicePixelRatio` for crisp mobile rendering\n    24→- Added `index.html` with viewport meta (no scaling), CSS reset for full-screen canvas\n    25→- Files changed: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `.gitignore`\n    26→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    27→  - Vite `create` won't scaffold into a non-empty directory — set up manually instead\n    28→  - PIXI.js v8 uses async init pattern: `const app = new Application(); await app.init({...})`\n    29→  - `autoDensity: true` + `resolution: devicePixelRatio` ensures sharp rendering on high-DPI phone screens\n    30→  - The viewport meta tag needs `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` to prevent pinch-zoom on mobile\n    31→---\n    32→\n    33→## 2026-03-02 - US-002\n    34→- Rendered 11 boxes in a 3-3-3-2 grid layout (Tier 4 at top, Tier 1 at bottom)\n    35→- Created `src/config.ts` with `BOX_LABELS` array — easy to swap labels\n    36→- Created `src/grid.ts` with `createGrid()` that positions boxes responsively\n    37→- Boxes have rounded corners, borders, centered text labels, and adapt to screen size\n    38→- Updated `src/main.ts` to import and call `createGrid(app)`\n    39→- Files changed: `src/config.ts` (new), `src/grid.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`\n    40→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    41→  - PIXI.js v8 `Graphics` API: use `bg.roundRect(...)` then `bg.fill(...)` then `bg.stroke(...)` — chained shape → fill → stroke\n    42→  - Box numbering is 0-based internally (array index) but 1-based in user-facing context — `BOX_LABELS[0]` = box 1\n    43→  - The grid ROWS constant maps visual rows (top-to-bottom) to box indices — bottom row has 2 boxes, rest have 3\n    44→  - `BoxInfo` interface is exported for future stories (line drawing will need `cx`, `cy` for connection endpoints)\n    45→  - Text `wordWrapWidth` should be box width minus padding to keep text readable\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## 2026-03-02 - US-003\n    49→- Implemented drag-to-connect interaction between boxes\n    50→- Created `src/connections.ts` with full pointer event handling (pointerdown on boxes, pointermove/pointerup on stage)\n    51→- Preview line (green, semi-transparent) follows finger during drag, disappears if drag ends outside a box\n    52→- Committed connections rendered as bezier curves (quadratic, with perpendicular offset) with arrowheads\n    53→- Lines start/end at box edges using ray-box intersection calculation\n    54→- Added `touch-action: none` to canvas CSS in `index.html` for reliable mobile touch handling\n    55→- Files changed: `src/connections.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n    56→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    57→  - PIXI v8 pointer events: set `eventMode = 'static'` and `hitArea` on containers for interaction\n    58→  - Use `app.stage.hitArea = app.screen` to capture stage-level pointer events\n    59→  - `pointercancel` event should be handled on mobile (browser can steal touch for gestures)\n    60→  - For bezier arrowheads: tangent at t=1 of quadratic bezier P0,CP,P2 is direction `P2 - CP`\n    61→  - Box edge intersection: compare `|dx|/halfW` vs `|dy|/halfH` to determine which edge is hit\n    62→  - `FederatedPointerEvent.global` gives coordinates in stage space (matches CSS coords with autoDensity)\n    63→---\n    64→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9148dbc1-4780-49bf-adf6-0e49414c1c59","uuid":"746f10ab-7f65-4adb-9c3f-bb17fab38256","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/jstoone/Sites/linjer/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- Project uses Vite + vanilla TypeScript (no framework)\n- PIXI.js v8 for canvas rendering — use `new Application()` then `await app.init(...)` pattern\n- Source code lives in `src/`\n- npm is the package manager (no bun/pnpm)\n- TypeScript strict mode enabled with `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters`\n- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for typecheck, `npx vite build` for build\n- Canvas is full-viewport with `resizeTo: window`, background `#1a1a2e`\n- Box labels live in `src/config.ts` as a `BOX_LABELS` string array (0-based index, box 1 = index 0)\n- Grid rendering lives in `src/grid.ts`, exports `createGrid(app)` → returns `BoxInfo[]`\n- `BoxInfo` has `index`, `container`, `cx`, `cy`, `w`, `h` — needed for line drawing in future stories\n- Connection logic lives in `src/connections.ts`, exports `setupConnections(app, boxes)` → returns `ConnectionManager`\n- `ConnectionManager` has `connections: Connection[]` (mutable array) and `redraw()` to re-render all lines\n- `Connection` interface: `{ source: number; target: number }` (0-based box indices)\n- Lines use quadratic bezier curves with perpendicular offset, arrowheads at target box edge\n- `touch-action: none` on canvas element prevents browser gestures from interfering with drag\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-001\n- Set up Vite + TypeScript project scaffold\n- Installed PIXI.js v8 and created full-viewport responsive canvas\n- Canvas uses `resizeTo: window`, `autoDensity: true`, and `devicePixelRatio` for crisp mobile rendering\n- Added `index.html` with viewport meta (no scaling), CSS reset for full-screen canvas\n- Files changed: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `.gitignore`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Vite `create` won't scaffold into a non-empty directory — set up manually instead\n  - PIXI.js v8 uses async init pattern: `const app = new Application(); await app.init({...})`\n  - `autoDensity: true` + `resolution: devicePixelRatio` ensures sharp rendering on high-DPI phone screens\n  - The viewport meta tag needs `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` to prevent pinch-zoom on mobile\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-002\n- Rendered 11 boxes in a 3-3-3-2 grid layout (Tier 4 at top, Tier 1 at bottom)\n- Created `src/config.ts` with `BOX_LABELS` array — easy to swap labels\n- Created `src/grid.ts` with `createGrid()` that positions boxes responsively\n- Boxes have rounded corners, borders, centered text labels, and adapt to screen size\n- Updated `src/main.ts` to import and call `createGrid(app)`\n- Files changed: `src/config.ts` (new), `src/grid.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - PIXI.js v8 `Graphics` API: use `bg.roundRect(...)` then `bg.fill(...)` then `bg.stroke(...)` — chained shape → fill → stroke\n  - Box numbering is 0-based internally (array index) but 1-based in user-facing context — `BOX_LABELS[0]` = box 1\n  - The grid ROWS constant maps visual rows (top-to-bottom) to box indices — bottom row has 2 boxes, rest have 3\n  - `BoxInfo` interface is exported for future stories (line drawing will need `cx`, `cy` for connection endpoints)\n  - Text `wordWrapWidth` should be box width minus padding to keep text readable\n---\n\n## 2026-03-02 - US-003\n- Implemented drag-to-connect interaction between boxes\n- Created `src/connections.ts` with full pointer event handling (pointerdown on boxes, pointermove/pointerup on stage)\n- Preview line (green, semi-transparent) follows finger during drag, disappears if drag ends outside a box\n- Committed connections rendered as bezier curves (quadratic, with perpendicular offset) with arrowheads\n- Lines start/end at box edges using ray-box intersection calculation\n- Added `touch-action: none` to canvas CSS in `index.html` for reliable mobile touch handling\n- Files changed: `src/connections.ts` (new), `src/main.ts`, `index.html`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - PIXI v8 pointer events: set `eventMode = 'static'` and `hitArea` on containers for interaction\n  - Use `app.stage.hitArea = app.screen` to capture stage-level pointer events\n  - `pointercancel` event should be handled on mobile (browser can steal touch for gestures)\n  - For bezier arrowheads: tangent at t=1 of quadratic bezier P0,CP,P2 is direction `P2 - CP`\n  - Box edge intersection: compare `|dx|/halfW` vs `|dy|/halfH` to determine which edge is hit\n  - `FederatedPointerEvent.global` gives coordinates in stage space (matches CSS coords with autoDensity)\n---\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
